make up my weird brain

00:21:45.630 --> 00:21:47.405
just went into her.

00:21:47.405 --> 00:21:49.530
And there's something very
scary about that, right?

00:21:49.530 --> 00:21:51.270
Just being like, I'm going
to put this out there.

00:21:51.270 --> 00:21:53.811
I'm going to write all the weird
shit that happens in my head

00:21:53.811 --> 00:21:55.230
on a daily basis in a character.

00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:56.896
People are like, that
character's crazy.

00:21:56.896 --> 00:21:57.900
And it's like, oh great.

00:21:57.900 --> 00:21:58.852
Thanks.

00:21:58.852 --> 00:22:00.299
[LAUGHING]

00:22:00.299 --> 00:22:02.340
People get really-- people
have a lot of feelings

00:22:02.340 --> 00:22:04.560
about her particularly.

00:22:04.560 --> 00:22:08.370
And I'm like, well, that's the
person who's most like me, so.

00:22:08.370 --> 00:22:08.970
But yeah.

00:22:08.970 --> 00:22:12.857
And so I feel like I just
wanted this collection that

00:22:12.857 --> 00:22:14.940
dealt with that in a way
that felt honest and felt

00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:16.290
like I was--

00:22:16.290 --> 00:22:18.810
I mean, honestly,
I'm only one person.

00:22:18.810 --> 00:22:23.020
I can only portray sort
of one type of experience

00:22:23.020 --> 00:22:27.130
or one person's
perception of experiences.

00:22:27.130 --> 00:22:29.099
But yeah, I just
wanted that honesty.

00:22:29.099 --> 00:22:30.640
It was really
important to me to have

00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:34.510
that sort of immediacy
and viscerality,

00:22:34.510 --> 00:22:35.879
and not sort of move around it.

00:22:35.879 --> 00:22:38.170
Because I feel like that's
the thing people like to do,

00:22:38.170 --> 00:22:42.840
is they get close to it and
they get afraid to dive in.

00:22:42.840 --> 00:22:46.270
And I was like, no, I
just want to be in there.

00:22:46.270 --> 00:22:48.487
So yeah.

00:22:48.487 --> 00:22:50.320
AUDIENCE: Once in a
