not read a book in the last 30

00:29:10.220 --> 00:29:10.720
years?

00:29:10.720 --> 00:29:12.720
I mean, it was literally
like that kind of list.

00:29:12.720 --> 00:29:16.270
And one woman, and it's like
the most famous female writer

00:29:16.270 --> 00:29:17.560
that we have right now, right?

00:29:20.667 --> 00:29:22.000
And I was really angry about it.

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:23.950
And then also in the
interview he said--

00:29:23.950 --> 00:29:26.230
someone asked him some
question and he was just like,

00:29:26.230 --> 00:29:28.190
my fiction is not political.

00:29:28.190 --> 00:29:30.130
I just don't believe in, like--

00:29:30.130 --> 00:29:32.080
I just don't want my
fiction to be political.

00:29:32.080 --> 00:29:34.600
Answered question.

00:29:34.600 --> 00:29:37.094
And my answer is, I don't
actually think it's possible.

00:29:37.094 --> 00:29:38.260
I don't think it's possible.

00:29:38.260 --> 00:29:42.350
Because even thinking that you
can write apolitical fiction

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.481
is in itself political.

00:29:44.481 --> 00:29:44.980
Right?

00:29:44.980 --> 00:29:48.430
So even a guy in a boat
having an adventure or person

00:29:48.430 --> 00:29:49.000
in a boat--

00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:50.380
who is that person?

00:29:50.380 --> 00:29:54.054
That's still a political
choice of a kind.

00:29:54.054 --> 00:29:55.970
So no, I actually don't
think those things can

00:29:55.970 --> 00:29:58.210
be separated from each other.

00:29:58.210 --> 00:30:01.270
And it's infuriating
to me that he

00:30:01.270 --> 00:30:03.995
is so uncurious about his
own craft and about the world

00:30:03.995 --> 00:30:05.320
that that is his response.

00:30:08.010 --> 00:30:10.285
It just really bothered
me, that with that platform

00:30:10.285 --> 00:30:12.040
he just wanted to
talk about Asimov.

00:30:12.040 --> 00:30:13.330
Which again, Asimov's great.

00:30:13.330 --> 00:30:14.590
But like, come on.

00:30:14.590 --> 00:30:16.170
[LAUGHING]

00:30:16.170 --> 00:30:18.430
And yeah.

00:30:18.430 --> 00:30:20.080
So no, I actually don't think--

00:30:20.080 --> 00:30:26.690
I mean, and I love a good,
exciting, pulpy piece of art

00:30:26.690 --> 00:30:28.430
as much as the next person.

00:30:28.430 --> 00:30:30.140
They give me a lot of pleasure.

00:30:30.140 --> 00:30:33.260
But also, that still
doesn't mean that-- like,

00:30:33.260 --> 00:30:35.230
I still come away from
the stupidest movie

00:30:35.230 --> 00:30:39.284
